  <eligibility>
    <study_pop>
      <textblock>
        In this study, there will be about 780 study subjects from 14 sites in Latin America.
        Subjects will be about 390 from clinical sites previously exposed to protocols for
        management of TBI, and about 390 from sites without prior exposure to protocols.  Half of
        the study subjects (about 390 total) will be treated in accordance with a consensus-based
        protocol.  Subjects will consist of patients with TBIs sufficiently severe to fulfill the
        inclusion criteria. To qualify, patients must be 13 or older and have a non-penetrating
        traumatic brain injury. The major criterion is severe TBI to be treated without the use of
        intracranial pressure monitoring
      </textblock>
    </study_pop>
    <sampling_method>Probability Sample</sampling_method>
    <criteria>
      <textblock>
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  Non-penetrating TBI

          -  Post-resuscitation Glasgow Coma Scale score (GCS) ≤ 8, and GCS Motor score ≤ 5, or
             Deterioration to those values within 48 hours of injury

          -  Age 13 years or older

          -  Consent to participate signed by Legally Authorized Representative (LAR)

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  GCS of 3 with bilateral fixed and dilated pupils and/or decision to not actively
             treat prior to enrolment into study

          -  Prisoner

          -  No consent

          -  Non-survivable injury

          -  Other (e.g., Pre-injury life expectancy under 1 year)

          -  Pre-existing neurological disability that would not allow follow-up
      </textblock>
    </criteria>
